CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 7, 1962, pg. 5, reads: "Scranton in Hill District - Congressman William W. Scranton, gubernatorial candidate on the Republican ticket, made a whirlwind tour of the city's Hill District, Monday morning, to see at first hand and to shake hands with voters. Accompanied by his wife, Mrs. Mary Scranton, he stopped at (1) The Courier, where we posed with city political leaders... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Unknown man, W. P. Young, Pennsylvania gubernatorial candidate William "Bill" Scranton, William Nunn Sr., unknown, Mary Scranton, and unknown standing in front of Pittsburgh Courier newspaper building
